**Emergency Steps:**  
- Use a cell phone or hard-wired phone to report outages, as cordless phones may not work without electricity.
- Use battery-operated flashlights instead of candles to prevent fire hazards.
- Unplug or turn off all electric and heat-producing appliances to prevent surges when power is restored.
- Keep refrigerator and freezer doors closed to preserve food during an outage.
- Check with neighbors to determine if the outage is widespread or localized to your home.

